I don't think that supporting java 7 is relevant nowadays. Many libs and frameworks already moved to Java 8. It will be more attractive, if we had Java 8. Of course this framework can be used within java 8, but official support is still important. And also the fact that Cactoos is Java 8 based will in fact leave us with no choice.

In terms of implementation: the codebase should be build with Java 8 (`jdk.version` property in maven) and also the `README.md` should mention that it is Java 8 framework. We can adopt Java 8 features lately in appropriate places.

Now we have [ExpirationDate](https://github.com/yegor256/takes/blob/master/src/main/java/org/takes/misc/ExpirationDate.java) which is a step towards re-usability. However it can be further improved. I propose to create
```
public interface Expires {
    String print();
}
```

It should print Expires string and we can have useful implementations. We need `Expires.Never` that will print `Expires=Thu, 01 Jan 1970 00:00:00 GMT` and `Expires.Hour` that will print expiration 1 hour after creation and `Expires.Date` that will replace `ExpirationDate`.  

This interface and implementations will be useful in various cases such as: [TkFlash](https://github.com/yegor256/takes/blob/master/src/main/java/org/takes/facets/flash/TkFlash.java) and in [RsFlash](https://github.com/yegor256/takes/blob/master/src/main/java/org/takes/facets/flash/RsFlash.java). There might be other useful usages for this interface.

